"""ClosingExecution Soccer concept nodes — person-free.

Scope: the ACT of CLOSING OUT a match — game-management and seeing out a lead in
the closing stage.  This family measures FINISHING behaviour: how a lead is
protected, how time and possession are managed to kill a game, the conversion of
a winning position into three points, and the mechanisms of conceding a late
equaliser.  Deliberately distinct from:
  - SpecialSituations (which owns set-piece / penalty / throw-in delivery states),
  - TempoControl (which owns pace / tempo behaviour as a general trait),
  - GamePhases (which owns the time-band / closing-stage window definitions),
  - DefensiveSchemes (which owns the structural defensive systems themselves).
Here the angle is always the EXECUTION of closing, not the static state or system.
"""
